review_blob: 22oz bottle. Deep brown with a big foamy light tan head. Aroma of chocolate, milk caramels, coffee and nuts. Flavor of milk chocolate, roasted coffee, caramel and no alcohol. Medium to full body with a soft mouth feel. Not bad, a bit sweet though.

Draft @ MS. Nearly black with a light tan head. Aroma is big coffee and chocolate with some caramel and roast. Flavor is heavy on the coffee with cocoa and some sweet malt, light alcohol. Fullish body with soft carbonation. Very nice coffee beer, lots of coffee and chocolate.
beer_name: Midnight Sun Ill Have Another (Coffee Stout)

review_blob: Draft @ MS. Clear amber orange with a tiny off white head. Aroma of citrus, spicy yeast, malt and herbal tea. Flavor is bitter and spicy with some light malt backbone. Medium to light body. Not bad.

Draft. Clear amber with a small head. Aroma of caramel, floral, citrus and pine. Flavor is firmly bitter with some slightly sweet malt and light dry alcohol. Medium body with average carbonation. Great IIPA, tasted very fresh.

Draft @ King St. Clearish deep brown with a light tan head. Aroma is doughy malt, toffee/caramel and light noble hops. Flavor is very malt but not overly sweet, fairly clean lager yeast profile and mild hop bitterness. Medium body with a smooth mouth feel. Really nice beer, lots of flavor and still very drinkable.

Draft @ ANC. Clear amber with a foamy off white head. Aroma of caramel, spicy yeast, citrus and light butterscotch. Flavor is more sweet caramel malt balanced with the spicy yeast esters and a firm hop bitterness. Medium body with average carbonation. Decent beer, but nothing too special.

22oz bottle. Clear copper with a light beige head. Aroma of bread dough and herbal hops mostly with light caramel and citrus. Flavor is balance with toasty malt and bitter hops. Medium body with average carbonation. Easy drinking beer.

22oz bottle. Nearly black with a medium sized tan head. Aroma of black malt, bittersweet chocolate, caramel and licorice. Flavor is bitter roasted malt, dark chocolate, caramel and light warming alcohol. Full body with a soft, smooth mouth feel. Solid imperial stout.
beer_name: Gigantic Most Premium Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: 22oz bottle. Clear amber/brown with a small light tan head. Aroma of dates, sugar, plums, toffee and alcohol. Flavor is more sweet malt and dark, dried fruit with some alcohol and vanilla. Medium body with a sweet finish. Not bad but really sweet, good in small doses.

16oz can thanks to GT. Light yellow with a small white head. Big hoppy aroma of tropical fruit, citrus, pine and melon. Flavor is mostly bitter hops with minimal malt sweetness and lots of hop flavor. Light thin body with average carbonation. Very good session beer, fresh and hoppy. Thanks GT.
beer_name: Pizza Port Ponto Sessionable India Pale Ale

review_blob: Growler. Clear golden yellow with a small white head. Aroma of herbal hops, bready malt and light spice. Clean light Malty flavor with medium hop bitterness. Light body average carbonation. Nice.
beer_name: Anchor Zymaster Series No. 1 California Lager

review_blob: 12oz bottle. Clear amber with an off white head and some lace. Aroma is doughy malt, caramel and light herbal hops. Flavor is malty with toast and bread and a light hop bitterness. Medium body with average carbonation. Average amber.

22oz bottle. Almost black with a thick tan head. Aroma of chocolate, rye, alcohol. caramel and vanilla. Flavor is sweet chocolate and caramel, sugary malt, rye spice and alcohol/vanilla. Full body with a thick mouth feel. Ok beer but pretty sweet and not very drinkable.

Growler. Clear deep amber with a small off white head. Aroma is big citrus, pine and caramel with some light alcohol. Flavor is bitter hops and caramel malt with some dry alcohol. Medium body with average carbonation. Really nice, very hoppy and balanced with the caramel malt.

Growler. Clear light amber with a small off white head. Aroma of toasty malt, pine, lemon and dough. Flavor is malty with a light hop bitterness and some alcohol. Medium body with soft carbonation. Nice.
beer_name: Big Sky Powder Hound Winter Ale

review_blob: Growler. Clear dark brown with a foamy light tan head. Aroma of bitter cocoa, coconut, coffee and black malt. Flavor is rich toasty coconut, chocolate, and robust coffee. Medium to full body with a smooth mouth feel. Great beer, lots of coconut character. One of the best things to come out of MSBC for a while.

Growler. Clear light amber with a small off white head. Aroma of caramel malt, citrus and floral hops. Flavor is malty with caramel, medium hop bitterness and a dry finish. Medium body with average carbonation. Good beer, very drinkable.

Growler. Slightly hazy amber with a small off white head. Aroma of caramel, butterscotch, citrus and grapes. Flavor is sweet malt and butterscotch with medium to light bitterness. Medium body with average carbonation. Ok, seems a bit off though.
beer_name: Kenai River Single Hop IPA (Pacific Gem)

review_blob: 750ml bottle. Dark brown with a foamy, long lasting light beige head. Aroma of toffee, alcohol, dried fruit and a light must and spice. Flavor is malty and slightly sweet with some spice and alcohol. Medium body with lively carbonation. Good beer, the sweetness subsides with age, great with a year or two on it.

12oz bottle. Clear amber with a thick, dense light beige head. Aroma of rye bread, toffee, alcohol, citrus and some pine. Flavor is malty mostly with some bitter hops and rye spice. Medium body with a dry alcohol head in the finish. Nice beer.

12oz bottle. Hazy amber with an off white head. Aroma of caramel, citrus, pine, flowers and dough. Flavor is balanced with bitter hops and sweet malt, some light alcohol. Medium body with a slightly dry finish. Solid IPA, tasted very fresh as well.
beer_name: Fish Tale Hodgsons Bitter End IPA

review_blob: 12oz bottle. Dark brown almost black with a tan head. Aroma of chocolate, dark fruit, coffee and black malt. Flavor is bitter roasted malt with rich chocolate and light alcohol. Full body with average carbonation. Really good beer, very rich but balanced.

12oz bottle. Very dark brown with a light tan head. Aroma of chocolate, coffee, burnt malt and light PacNW hops. Flavor is roasty bitter malt, chocolate, caramel sweetness with light hops and alcohol. Full body with a smooth mouth feel. Solid Imp Stout.
beer_name: Left Coast Voo Doo American Stout

review_blob: 22oz bottle. Clear amber with a beige head. Aroma of bready/doughy malt, caramel and pine. Flavor is malty with a firm hop bitterness, no alcohol taste. Medium body with average carbonation. Really nice amber.

Draft @ GBH. Clear red/brown with a small off white head. Aroma is light peat smoke, toffee and fruity. Flavor is malty with light fruity yeast and alcohol. Medium body with a smooth mouth feel. Nice beer, very drinkable.

Draft @ Cafe Amsterdam. Clear deep amber with a small off white head. Aroma of toffee, dried fruit, spicy yeast esters and light alcohol. Taste is smooth malt with a light zesty flavor and some alcohol warming. Medium body with average carbonation. Really nice beer, flavorful and not overly sweet.

Draft @ Humpys. Clear reddish amber with a tiny off white head. Aroma is mostly fragrant flowers with some citrus and malt. Flavor is sweet malt and perfume with a medium bitterness and light alcohol warming. Medium body with slightly low carbonation. Not a big fan of this one, too perfumey for me.

22oz bottle. Clear dark brown with a fizzy light tan head. Aroma of chocolate mostly with some coffee, caramel and light floral. Flavor is more chocolate and roasted malt with a caramel sweetness and mild alcohol taste. Medium to full body with average carbonation. Decent porter but nothing too special.
beer_name: 10 Barrel / Bluejacket / Stone Suede Imperial Porter

review_blob: Draft @ GBH. Clear golden with a small white head. Aroma of grainy malt, spicy yeast esters and honey. Flavor is crisp malt with some zesty and light bitterness in the finish. Medium to light body with average carbonation. Pretty good beer, refreshing and very drinkable.

Draft @ GBH. Clear amber with a tiny white head. Aroma of sugary malt, spicy yeast esters and light citrus. Flavor is sweet candi sugar and malt with a light zesty finish, mild alcohol warming. Medium body with light carbonation. Decent but a bit sweet.

Growler. Hazy amber/orange with a foamy off white head. Aroma is mostly all tropical fruit with some citrus peel and sweet malt. Flavor is balanced but on the bitter side (just how I like my IPAs), nice malt backbone and light dry alcohol. Medium to light body with average carbonation. Great beer, super fresh and hoppy.

750ml bottle. Dark brown with a small dense tan head. Aroma of tart cherry, cocoa, damp wood and funky bacteria. Flavor is bitter chocolate malt, tart cherry, dry oak and light sour, no alcohol taste. Medium body with a soft mouth feel. Good beer, all the different components come together fairly well but not one Id want to drink very often.

Stubby bottle. Clear amber with a tiny head. Aroma is mostly caramel malt with some light fruitiness and bread dough. Flavor is doughy/grainy malt with a very faint hop bitterness. Medium body with weak carbonation. Ok beer but not too drinkable for me.
beer_name: Full Sail Session Fest Red Lager

review_blob: Growler. Clear amber with a small off white head. Aroma of peach juice, citrus and caramel. Flavor of peach and other light fruit that is on the sweet side with a mild hop bitterness. Medium body with a slightly syrupy mouth feel. Well you definitely get the peach but its a bit on the sweet side for my taste.

Bottle. Clear golden yellow with a foamy white head. Aroma of bready pils malt and some spicy/herbal noble hops. Flavor is clean malt with a mild bitterness. Light body with a crisp finish. Average beer all around.

Growler. Cloudy golden yellow with a foamy white head. Aroma is fruity wheat mostly with some citrus and spice. Flavor is more wheat with some banana/clove yeast esters and light hop bitterness. Light body with average carbonation. Decent wheat beer but dont really see this as an IPA.

22oz bottle. Clear amber/orange with a foamy white head. Aroma of tropical fruit, vegetal, grassy, citrus and some biscuit malt. Flavor is malty with a medium to low hop bitterness and some "green" hop taste. Medium body with average carbonation. Not bad.
beer_name: New Belgium Hop Kitchen  #3 - Fresh Hop

review_blob: Growler. Clear deep amber with a small head. Aroma of toffee, dark fruit, bourbon and oak. Flavor is more toffee with boozy bourbon, vanilla and light dry oak. Medium body with a smooth feel. Nice beer, great barrel character.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Reserve Barrel Aged Brrrbon

review_blob: Growler. Very dark brown, nearly black with a small deep tan head. Aroma of black malt, chocolate, licorice, coffee and ash. Flavor is lots of bitter roasted malt, molasses, coffee and some alcohol. Full body with a smooth, lush mouth feel. This one if very strong, rich and bitter but nicely balanced.

12oz bottle. Murky copper/brown with a small beige head. Aroma of spice, pumpernickel bread, caramel and fruity yeast esters. Flavor is toasty malt, caramel, spice and yeast. Medium body with a smooth mouth feel. Different fall beer but good, nicely balanced and not overly spiced.

750ml from Beernbourbon. Clearish deep amber with a foamy light beige head and some lacing. Aroma of sweet potato pie, spice, graham cracker and maple syrup. Flavor is pumpkin pie with lots of malt, light spice and no alcohol taste. Medium body with average carbonation. Great fall beer, lots of pie character.

Draft from the latest batch. Clear light brown with a small light tan head. Aroma of doughy malt, coffee, nuts and light cocoa. Flavor is more doughy malt, robust coffee and rich malt. Medium body with a soft, smooth mouth fee. Really nice beer, very malty all around but the coffee adds a nice balance and drinkability.

22oz bottle. Murky rusty brown with a spotty light beige head. Aroma of musty wet wood, malt vinegar, cherries and light fruit. Flavor is fairly tart upfront with sour vinegar, light caramel malt and a dry alcohol. Medium to light body with a dry mouth feel. Have had this one numerous times, always a nice beer if your in the mood.

Growler. Clear amber with a small off white head. Aroma of caramel malt, herbal hops and light fruitiness. Flavor is mostly mild caramel malt with a faint hop presence and fairly clean yeast. Medium body with a smooth mouth fee. Solid amber, goes down easy.

Growler. Slightly hazy amber/orange with a small off white head. Aroma of citrus peel, malt, light fruit and caramel. Flavor is balanced bitter hops and sweet malt, no alcohol taste. Medium to light body with average carbonation. Solid beer, very drinkable.

750ml bottle. Clear deep amber with a small fizzy head. Aroma of dates, toffee, alcohol, rich doughy malt and light spice. Flavor is rich caramel malt, bread dough, raisin and light alcohol. Medium to full body with a smooth mouth feel. Really great beer, rich and flavorful but not overly sweet.

750ml bottle. Dark brown with a huge, foamy khaki head. Aroma of dark bready malt, citrus, coffee and cocoa. Flavor is rich doughy malt, chocolate, coffee with mildly bitter hops and no alcohol taste. Medium body with a smooth mouth feel. Ok beer but not a lot of hop bitterness or aroma.

Growler. Hazy amber with a tiny off white head. Aroma is citrusy Pac NW hops and sweet sugary honey malt. Flavor is malty with light hop bitterness and light yeast esters. Medium to light body with soft carbonation. Not bad but nothing makes this really stand out.
beer_name: Fish Tale Beyond The Pale Ale

review_blob: 22oz bottle. Clear light amber with an off white head and some lacing. Aroma of flowers, citrus, pine, caramel and bubble gum. Flavor is malty, fruity esters medium bitter hops and light dry alcohol. Medium body with a soft mouth feel. Good IPA.
beer_name: New Belgium The Trip XVIII (El Dorado Fresh Hop IPA)

review_blob: Growler. Clearish light amber with a medium off white head. Aroma of citrus, spicy rye, caramel and toast. Flavor is bitter hops, rye bread and light alcohol. Medium body with a dry bitter finish. Pretty good, the best Arkose beer Ive tried.
